<text>Inputting and outputting

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

When you save a MW page, the current state of the Simulator will be saved as well. In addition to this, you can save a state to a file that is not part of a MW page. The file can be loaded to a Simulator later.

To do this, you just need to use the &quot;Save Model As&quot; and &quot;Open Model&quot; items of the File Menu of the Simulator. Or simply right-click (or CTRL+click on Mac OS X without a multiple-button mouse) on an empty spot of the Simulator&apos;s screen, and select the corresponding items from the pop-up menu.

Practice

You may play with the following simulator about outputting and inputting a model&apos;s state. Run the simulation for a while, stop it and then save the state to a file. Repeat for a few times. And then load back the saved files.

 
